#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdocument-composer.md:1
msgid "Document Composer"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdocument-composer.md:3
msgid ""
"The Document Composer lets you author formal government decision documents "
"(*beschikkingen*) as structured templates inside the Linked Data Explorer. "
"Templates are zone-based, block-driven, and bound to Operaton process "
"variables — so a document authored here can be rendered at runtime by "
"MijnOmgeving for any completed process instance."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdocument-composer.md:12
msgid "Three-panel layout"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdocument-composer.md:14
msgid ""
"The Composer uses the same three-panel layout convention as the BPMN Modeler "
"and Chain Builder."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdocument-composer.md:16
msgid ""
"**Left panel** — Document list. Shows all documents stored in `localStorage` "
"with create, rename, delete, and **Save as…** actions. An **EXAMPLE** badge "
"marks the read-only seed document; user-created documents carry a **WIP** "
"badge."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdocument-composer.md:17
msgid ""
"**Centre panel** — Zone canvas. Renders the document zones in A4-style "
"layout. Blocks are dragged onto zones from the left panel's Content library, "
"and can be reordered or moved between zones by dragging."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdocument-composer.md:18
msgid ""
"**Right panel** — Bindings. Links `{{placeholder}}` tokens in rich-text "
"blocks to Operaton process variable keys. Only visible when a document is "
"active."
msgstr ""

